events.name: Alabama Crimson Tide at Georgia Bulldogs

headlines.description: In a dramatic twist on last season's national championship game, Jalen Hurts came off the bench to pass for one touchdown and run for another in the fourth quarter, rallying No. 1 Alabama to a 35-28 win over No. 4 Georgia for the Southeastern...
headlines.shortLinkText: Hurts rallies No. 1 Alabama to 35-28 win over No. 4 Georgia

headlines.description: Travis Etienne ran for 156 yards and two touchdowns, Trevor Lawrence threw two short scoring passes to Tee Higgins and No. 2 Clemson beat Pitt 42-10 on Saturday night to become the first team to win four straight Atlantic Coast Conference championships.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 2 Clemson clobbers Pitt 42-10 for 4th straight ACC title

video.headline: Clemson RB escapes for 75-yard TD on opening play

headlines.description: Kyler Murray threw for 379 yards and three touchdowns as No. 5 Oklahoma beat No. 9 Texas 39-27 in the Big 12 championship game Saturday, with the Sooners avenging their only loss and making their case for a return to the College Football Playoff.
headlines.shortLinkText: CFP hopeful No. 5 Oklahoma beats No. 9 Texas for Big 12

video.headline: Oklahoma pulls away from Texas to win Big 12 title

events.name: Northwestern Wildcats at Ohio State Buckeyes

headlines.description: Dwayne Haskins added five more touchdown passes to his single-season record Saturday and No. 6 Ohio State relied on its staunch defense to hold off a second-half charge from No. 21 Northwestern for a 45-24 victory to claim its second straight Big Ten...
headlines.shortLinkText: Ohio State pulls away from Wildcats to win Big Ten crown

video.headline: Haskins' 5th TD seals Ohio State's Big Ten title

headlines.description: Darriel Mack shrugged off two early turnovers to rush for three second-half touchdowns and rally No. 7 UCF to a 56-41 victory over Memphis in the American Athletic Conference championship game Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mack shines, No. 7 UCF beats Memphis 56-41 for AAC title

video.headline: UCF comes back from 17 down to beat Memphis

events.name: Fresno State Bulldogs at Boise State Broncos

headlines.description: Ronnie Rivers scored on a 1-yard run in overtime to give No. 24 Fresno State a 19-16 victory over No. 19 Boise State on Saturday night in the snowy Mountain West championship game.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 24 Fresno State outlasts No. 19 Boise State in snow

events.name: Drake Bulldogs at Iowa State Cyclones

headlines.description: David Montgomery ran for 145 yards and two touchdowns and No. 24 Iowa State barely survived a near-upset by non-scholarship FCS school Drake on Saturday, winning 27-24.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 24 Iowa State barely survives, beats FCS Drake 27-24

video.headline: Purdy and Jones link up for Iowa State TD

events.name: Louisiana Ragin' Cajuns at Appalachian State Mountaineers

headlines.description: Zac Thomas had two long touchdown runs, Darrynton Evans set up another score with a 97-yard kickoff return and Appalachian State defeated Louisiana-Lafayette 30-19 in the Sun Belt Conference championship game on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thomas guides Appalachian State to Sun Belt title

video.headline: App State's Thomas scores 35-yard TD on 4th down

events.name: East Carolina Pirates at NC State Wolfpack

headlines.description: Reggie Gallaspy Jr. ran for 220 yards and two touchdowns to set a program single-season TD record and help North Carolina State beat East Carolina 58-3 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: NC State beats East Carolina 58-3 in regular-season finale

video.headline: NC State interception sets up Gallaspy TD

events.name: Akron Zips at South Carolina Gamecocks

headlines.description: Deebo Samuel caught two touchdown passes and recovered a bad snap on a punt in the end zone for another score as South Carolina beat Akron 28-3 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: South Carolina beats Akron 28-3 in messy makeup game

video.headline: Samuel scores 3rd TD of 1st half for South Carolina

events.name: Marshall Thundering Herd at Virginia Tech Hokies

headlines.description: Virginia Tech is bowl-eligible for the 26th straight year after beating Marshall in a game scheduled two weeks ago with the hope of keeping the Hokies' streak alive.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hokies handle Marshall to keep bowl streak alive

video.headline: Willis finds Grimsley for 46-yard Hokies TD

events.name: James Madison Dukes at Colgate Raiders

headlines.description: It wasn't so much the Mike Houston coaching rumors proved to be too big of a distraction when James Madison was eliminated from the FCS playoffs on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Colgate's game-ending FG eliminates James Madison

video.headline: Colgate's game-winning field goal advances it to quarterfinal

events.name: UAB Blazers at Middle Tennessee Blue Raiders

headlines.description: Spencer Brown ran for 156 yards and a touchdown, Nick Vogel put UAB ahead with a field goal with 3:23 remaining, and the Blazers, who reinstated their program last season after a two-year hiatus, beat Middle Tennessee in the Conference USA championship.
headlines.shortLinkText: UAB wins C-USA title 4 years after cutting sport

events.name: Norfolk State Spartans at Liberty Flames

headlines.description: Kentory Matthews rushed for 151 yards and four touchdowns and Frankie Hickson ran for 100 yards and a score to power Liberty to a 52-17 romp over FCS-member Norfolk State on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Matthews' 4 TDs propels Liberty past Norfolk State 52-17

video.headline: Juwan Carter pass intercepted for a TD Rion Davis return for 22 yds for a TD (Aaron Peart KICK)

events.name: Stanford Cardinal at California Golden Bears

headlines.description: Cameron Scarlett caught a short pass from K.J. Costello and raced 46 yards for one of his two touchdowns, Paulson Adebo intercepted two passes and Stanford relied on its defense to win its ninth straight Big Game, 23-13 over California on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stanford wins 9th straight Big Game, 23-13 over California

video.headline: Garbers picked off on incredible 1-handed INT
